---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Aftercare Instructions"
  description="How to care for your new tattoo or piercing from Catharsis Body Art."
>
  <section class="section-block">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">Aftercare</span>
      <div>
        <h1 class="section-heading">Heal with intention</h1>
        <p class="section-subhead">
          Follow these steps to protect your fresh work and ensure the best
          possible heal. Every body is different‚Äîwhen in doubt, reach out.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block">
    <div class="aftercare-grid">
      <article class="luxe-card aftercare-card">
        <h2>Saniderm bandage</h2>
        <div class="callout info">
          <h3>Heads up</h3>
          <p>
            All artists apply Saniderm immediately after your session. If you
            have adhesive or latex allergies, tell us before your appointment so
            we can wrap with a traditional bandage.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ol class="steps-list">
          <li>
            <span class="step-badge">24-48h</span>
            Leave the bandage on for 24‚Äì48 hours. Seeing plasma, ink, or blood collect
            under the film is normal‚Äîdon‚Äôt peel it early.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="step-badge">Release</span>
            Gently push pooled fluid toward the edge and blot with a clean towel
            if it becomes uncomfortable.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="step-badge">Shower safe</span>
            Saniderm is water-resistant‚Äîquick showers are fine. Skip soaking, baths,
            pools, or hot tubs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="step-badge">Remove</span>
            Peel the bandage off slowly in the shower under lukewarm water, pulling
            it back over itself‚Äînot straight up.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </article>

      <article class="luxe-card aftercare-card">
        <h2>First two weeks</h2>
        <div class="callout success">
          <h3>Lotion routine</h3>
          <p>
            After removing Saniderm, apply a thin layer of unscented moisturizer
            (Aquaphor, Lubriderm, etc.) 2‚Äì3 times daily for two weeks or until
            skin normalizes. Less is more‚Äîavoid clogging pores.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="emoji-list">
          <li>
            <span>‚òÄÔ∏è</span>
            Avoid direct sun, tanning beds, and harsh UV until fully healed. If you
            must go outside, cover the area.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>üèÉ</span>
            Skip the gym, pools, and high-sweat activities for 4‚Äì5 days while it‚Äôs
            bandaged. Too soon risks infection.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>üö´</span>
            Do not scratch, pick, or peel flaking skin. Let the healing cycle run
            naturally to protect detail and color.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block">
    <div class="aftercare-grid">
      <article class="luxe-card aftercare-card">
        <h2>Long-term care</h2>
        <div class="callout warm">
          <h3>Protect your investment</h3>
          <p>
            Once healed, apply SPF 15+ whenever you‚Äôre in the sun. UV rays break
            down pigment rapidly. Keep skin hydrated year-round.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="dot-list">
          <li>
            Expect surface healing in ~2 weeks; complete healing can take up to
            3 months.
          </li>
          <li>
            Saniderm can speed things up, but everyone‚Äôs timeline is different.
          </li>
          <li>Schedule free touch-ups within 3 months for normal wear.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="luxe-card aftercare-card danger">
        <h2>Warning signs</h2>
        <div class="callout danger">
          <h3>Contact a doctor if you notice</h3>
          <ul class="dot-list">
            <li>Persistent redness spreading from the tattooed area</li>
            <li>Green or yellow discharge or a foul odor</li>
            <li>Fever, chills, or flu-like symptoms</li>
